<p> Real quick, as I just did this and need to get it captured. It is very rough as I&#8217;m sanitizing it as I go, so I hope I don&#8217;t introduce errors. </p>
<p> If you have a custom domain in Proton Mail or multiple email accounts, make sure you enable <b>Split Addresses</b> in the Proton Mail Bridge app (v3.15.1). In my example I&#8217;m only setting up my primary for right now. </p>
<p> The bridge will display the values for <code>HOST</code>, <code>USER</code>, <code>PORT</code>, and <code>TLSTYPE</code>. </p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<label class="org-src-name"><em></em></label></p>
<pre class="src src-conf" id="nil">IMAPAccount proton
Host 127.0.0.1
User example@proton.me
UseKeychain yes
Port 1143
TLSType STARTTLS
CertificateFile ~/.maildir/certificates/cert.pem

IMAPStore proton-remote
Account proton

MaildirStore proton-local
SubFolders Verbatim
Path ~/.maildir/proton/
Inbox ~/.maildir/proton/INBOX

Channel proton
Far :proton-remote:
Near :proton-local:
Patterns *
Create Near
Sync All
Expunge Both
SyncState *

<span style="color: #505050;"># </span><span style="color: #505050;">UseKeychain yes|no</span>
<span style="color: #505050;">#        </span><span style="color: #505050;">Whether to use the macOS Keychain to obtain the password.  (Default: no)</span>

<span style="color: #505050;">#        </span><span style="color: #505050;">The neccessary keychain item can be created this way:</span>

<span style="color: #505050;">#               </span><span style="color: #505050;">security add-internet-password -r imap -s Host -a User -w password [ -T /path/to/mbsync ]</span>
</pre>
</div>
<p> Once the account is set up in the app, click the gear  icon on the upper left. Scroll down until you see <b>Export TLS certificates</b>. Export them to <code>~/.maildir/certificates/</code> in my example (or wherever you want to put them &amp; adjust the config accordingly). </p>
<p> <b>NOTE</b>: <code>SSLType</code> seen in other configs is deprecated. </p>
<p> <b>NOTE</b>: <code>TLSType</code> must be set, cannot be <code>NONE</code> </p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<label class="org-src-name"><em></em></label></p>
<pre class="src src-shell" id="nil">security add-internet-password -r imap -j mu4e -s 127.0.0.1 -a example@proton.me -w <span style="color: #2544bb;">"YourPasswordAsDisplayedInProtonMailBridge"</span>
</pre>
</div>
<p> This in conjunction with the <code>UseKeychain</code> config setting above will trigger mbsync to look in the MacOs keychain for the authentication information. </p>
